sub_title: English Second Language Teacher (Native Speaker) at Montessorischool Parijsch  & Infinity College
summary:
People describe me as: hard-working, motivated, flexible, honest, open-minded, gets-the-job-done, rational yet creative.
Although I have leader qualities, I prefer to be in the crowd. Although I am honest, I prefer to listen before giving my opinion. Although I am flexible, my faith and family come first. Although I work hard, the process is more important to me than the outcome.

I am highly sensitive and strong willed, I have a double nationality,  I have a background in sports, I have lived in three different countries, I have acquired two languages but can understand four.

Although Iâ€™ve been teaching in education (primary & secondary) for most of my working life, I believe it only defines a parts of who I am. Besides developing in a work environment, the past ten years I have also developed my personality, become a wife and a mother. All these attributes I take with me in my day to day activities.

At the end of the day, I strive to stay close to who I am as a person and give the best I can.
